The paper deals with improving the robustness of deep learning models to input noise, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves training a learned optimizer, which falls under the sub-category of optimization algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a task in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
